$ VBA: datatype variant
@ variant

The *actual* datatype of a variant variable is determined at runtime. Hence the name.

As long as a variant variable is unitizlied, it is said to be
→ development/languages/VBA/language/null-and-nothing-etc#vba-empty[empty]. → development/languages/VBA/functions#vba-isEmpty[`isEmpty()`] can be used to determine if a variant was initialized.

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes[datatypes]

  → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/variant
